# Builder.io Fusion — Project Rules

These rules apply to every task. Do not deviate from them.

## Dev Server
- Always start the dev server with `npm run dev -- --webpack`
- Never use `next dev` without `--webpack` — Turbopack is incompatible with Builder Dev Tools

## Config & Model Names
- Never hardcode Builder model names as string literals in pages or components
- All model names and the API key live in `config.ts` — always read from there:
  - `config.envs.builderApiKey`
  - `config.models.page`, `config.models.blogArticle`, etc.
- When adding a new model, add its name to `config.ts` first before using it anywhere

## Builder SDK Usage
- Never use `<Content>` directly — always use the wrapper:
  `import { RenderBuilderContent } from "@/components/builder/RenderBuilderContent"`
- Always guard `notFound()` with both editing and preview checks:
  `if (!content && !isEditing() && !isPreviewing()) return notFound()`
- Always guard `subscribeToEditor` with a `builder.preview` URL param check to prevent
  "Model Name Mismatch" errors — see `docs/skills/builder-io.md` for the exact pattern
- For full SDK patterns, route types, and blog model patterns: `docs/skills/builder-io.md`
- For design system components, tokens, and WCAG rules: `docs/skills/design-system.md`

## Security
- Never use `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` on Builder HTML fields without DOMPurify sanitization

## Imports & Paths
- Always use the `@/` path alias for internal imports — never use relative paths like `../../`
- Import design system components from the barrel: `@/components/design-system`

## Testing
- Tests live in `tests/` — mirroring the component structure (`tests/design-system/`, `tests/blog/`, `tests/layout/`)
- Run with `npm test` (headless) or `npm run test:ui` (interactive)
- Two fixture pages serve as test harnesses — do not link them from the app:
  - `app/design-system/page.tsx` — design system components (Button, Badge, Input, Card, Typography, Counter)
  - `app/test/blog-components/page.tsx` — blog components with static mock data
- For full conventions, gotchas, and fixture page patterns: `docs/skills/testing.md`
